description.narrative: By 2020, 20,000 boys and 20,000 girls from 200 schools benefit from improved, child-friendly, gender appropriate and inclusive WASH facilities., which contributes to Equitable Access To Quality Education, Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid), Wash In Schools And Ecd Centres, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, children, especially the most disadvantaged children, benefit from inclusive, quality early learning and basic education with improved learning outcomes attained.

description.narrative: The National WASH in Schools Strategy (WinS) and Costed Action Plan was approved by MoEYS this year. This WinS, developed with UNICEF support, promotes a comprehensive, long-term approach, and was prepared with the engagement of various stakeholders: schools (students, teachers, principals), municipal authorities, Development Partners, and representatives from the Ministries of Education, Health, and Public Works. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:06/02/2020
